job summary:
We are seeking a full time nurse practitioner or physician assistant with cardiac experience preferred, to join our pre-op clinic at CMC Main in Charlotte, NC. The CMC Main clinic is fast paced and serves as the pre-op clinic for both surgery and anesthesia. The nurse practitioner/physician assistant will work closely with the Southeast Anesthesiology pre-op anesthesia team and CMC hospital staff as they perform surgical pre-ops. The clinic is generally staffed between 7:30am and 4:30pm M-F. There are no weekends and there is no call associated with this position. The nurse practitioner/physician assistant in the CMC pre-op clinic will perform the following duties:


• Perform initial patient evaluations and follow-up evaluations, to include history/physical and diagnosis/treatment;

• Document in hospital and outpatient charts;

• Order pertinent labs, medications, diagnostic studies;

• Prescribe appropriate medications;

• Order other therapies when indicated;

• Communicate patient results with anesthesiologists and surgeons;

• Perform other duties related to pre-op clinical care and/or operations as assigned.


Charlotte is the largest city in the state of North Carolina. The city enjoys a high quality of life with temperate weather. Residents enjoy a host of outdoor recreational activities, excellent schools, numerous opportunities for continuing education, the best available health care, a low unemployment rate, diverse culinary offerings, fantastic shopping, arts, cultural events and professional sports.


We offer competitive salaries and excellent benefits including:


• Health (choice of two PPO options), life, vision, dental and disability insurance

• 401(k) with potential company percentage match

• Annual CME allowance

• Potential for relocation assistance

• Employee stock purchase plan

• Stability in an organization with more than 35 years of healthcare industry experience

• Opportunities to participate alongside physicians in quality improvement initiatives

• Professional liability insurance and assistance with mandatory hospital credentialing and state licensing, and reimbursement of associated fees.


